KPIValue.definition: Key performance indicator values calculated for a specific renovation project and scenario.

maxValue.definition: Upper limit to define a KPI Value.

relatedValue.definition: Numeric quantity of a KPI value.

tolerance.definition: Tolerance error in the value of a KPI.

minValue.definition: Lower limit to define a KPI Value.

unitOfMeasure.definition: Indicates the unit of measure of a kpi value.

Element.definition: A building represents a structure that provides shelter for its occupants or contents and stands in one place. The building is also used to provide a basic element within the spatial structure hierarchy for the components of a building project (together with site, storey, and space).

ifcIdentifier.definition: Global identifier in the IFC file

performedAtSpace.definition: Relate a process with a space

executionStatus.definition: Indicates the state of the work order - possible values: ABORTED, COMPLETED, DOWNLOADED, PAUSED, RUNNING

relatedProject.definition: Relation to connect a process or workorder with a project.

executedBy.definition: Indicates who is responsable for executing a process or task

relatedKPI.definition: Relates an entity with specific kpi definitions.

relatedTask.definition: Indicates the tasks involved in a process

performedAtStorey.definition: Relate a process with a storey

HealthSafetyIssue.definition: Health and safety issues related to an specific task.

message.definition: Message describing the health and safety issue.

relatedStorey.definition: Relates an issue with a storey.

relatedSpace.definition: Relates an issue with a space.

KPI.definition: Key performance indicators related to building renovation projects

relatedKPIValue.definition: Relates an entity with specific kpi values.

result.definition: Indicates the state of the task, possible values are: YES (done), NO (not done), PROBLEM (finished with problems), STARTED, READY

relatedIssue.definition: Relates an specific task to an issue.

executedBy.definition: Indicates who is responsable for executing a process or task

relatedKPI.definition: Relates an entity with specific kpi definitions.

Project.definition: A project is a temporary endeavor undertaken to achieve defined objectives (definition taken from DBpedia).

relatedProcess.definition: Relates a project with its processes

UnitOfMeasure.definition: The unit of measure is a standard for measurement of a quantity, such as a Property. For example, Power is a property and Watt is a unit of power that represents a definite predetermined power: when we say 10 Watt, we actually mean 10 times the definite predetermined power called "watt". Our definition is based on the definition of unit of measure in the Ontology of units of Measure (OM). We propose here a list of some units of measure that are relevant for the purpose of the Smart Appliances ontology, but this list can be extended.

Space.definition: A space represents an area or volume bounded actually or theoretically. Spaces are areas or volumes that provide for certain functions within a building.

ifcIdentifier.definition: Global identifier in the IFC file

Storey.definition: The building storey has an elevation and typically represents a (nearly) horizontal aggregation of spaces that are vertically bound.

ifcIdentifier.definition: Global identifier in the IFC file
